}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C0A2905077AA4DE19EC669C7A5F65F91","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Check tissue before grinding.  Tissue should be brittle and break into pieces when pinched with fingers. If tissue is soft and bends, incubate with silica gel for a longer period of time. Note that silica gel orange and similar silica gels contain a color indicator.  If silica is saturated with water and color changes, replace with fresh silica. Silica gel can be dried and re-used. Tissue can be stored for many months to indefinitely at room temperature as long as silica is not saturated with water.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":172800,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":902030,"guid":"21FDBC406DD511EA97E3CF38AE92EC08","previous_id":895389,"previous_guid":"D00485E063B111EABE8E951245B7750A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BF86CFEBD16848F084C92FB074AE09FB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Wash and elute DNA"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D61D40BC0C6D41F597408B79B25B380D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">To ensure complete removal of RNA, incubate DNA <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> . DNA can then be concentrated by EtOH or PEG precipitation. We recommend PEG precipitation as it can help remove any protein impurities. We use a final concentration of 13.3% PEG 6000 and 10 mM MgCl2, with a <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  incubation at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  followed by a  <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  centrifugation. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"46D04F606DD511EA97E3CF38AE92EC08","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":0,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"4CA7D2F06DD511EA9